<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-05-09T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-05-09T02:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/128: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-09T16:00:00+09:00"><hi rend="italic">May 9, 1921—4
                                        p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 9—12:49
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>161. Following from Peking received today: “184, May 6, 7 p.m. Japanese
                            Legation has made public substance of exchange of notes between Japanese
                            and American Governments regarding Federal wireless.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>